By replacing `sorry` with `by exact le_top`, we complete the proof, as all other steps are correctly set up to use this fact. The rest of the proof follows by composing the smooth maps and applying the chain rule appropriately. 

This approach ensures that the proof is concise and leverages the properties of `ℕ∞` correctly. No additional libraries or complex arguments are needed beyond the basic understanding that `n ≤ ⊤` always holds.
